-- Shell sees Sakhalin-2 LNG exports after late 2008
-- 
-- Tue Apr 29, 2008 5:46am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/29/us-shell-sakhalin-idUSWLB069220080429

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - Russia's Sakhalin-2 should begin exporting liquefied natural gas (LNG) shortly after construction finishes late this year, Royal Dutch Shell's ( RDSa.L ) Chief Financial Officer Peter Voser said on Tuesday. 

 Sakhalin-2 is controlled by Russian gas export monopoly Gazprom ( GAZP.MM ), with involvement by Shell, Mitsui ( 8031.T ) and Mitsubishi ( 8058.T ). (Reporting by  Alex Lawler ; editing by Peg Mackey)